After testing the three regression models, Linear Regression performed the best overall. It had the lowest MAE and MSE valies and the highest R² score at about 0.29. This means it predicted the diabetes dataset more accurately than the other models. The Decision Treee model performed the worst and even produced a negative R² value. The K-Neighbors model performed better than the Decison Treee but still had hihger errors than Linear Regression.
